			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<a href="http://www.beaffinitive.com" target="_blank">Affinitive</a>, a social marketing solutions pioneer and Facebook Preferred Marketing Developer (PMD), is looking for an amazing, social media-savvy Technical Project Manager to join our team. You will be responsible for overseeing the consulting, requirements gathering, design, development, testing, and deployment of Affinitive&#39;s social media-based technology solutions. This includes requirements gathering, developing specs, scheduling and resource planning, and managing members of our development team. You should have an established background in developing client-facing solutions, strong technical ability, excellent project management skills, great communication skills, and a motivation to achieve results in a fast paced environment.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Lead the overall scoping, planning, execution, and on-time delivery of engineering projects</li>
<li>
Define resources, schedules, and budgets</li>
<li>
Create strategies for risk mitigation and contingency planning</li>
<li>
Maintain timelines and develop launch/release plans for projects</li>
<li>
Efficiently identify project issues and work for timely resolution</li>
<li>
Create and maintain technical and project documentation</li>
<li>
Ensure that technology standards and best practices are maintained across the organization</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree with 4+ years of experience successfully managing and supporting client-facing and internal web-based software projects through the entire software development lifecycle (consumer-facing web mobile applications, websites, cloud-based SaaS platforms)</li>
<li>
Experience with project management methodologies (Agile, Waterfall, Scrum)</li>
<li>
Project experience with web technologies, such as PHP, MySQL, MongoDB, Javascript, Facebook Platform, other social APIs</li>
<li>
High level of competency in Microsoft Office applications and web-based project management/collaboration tools (<a href="http://www.quora.com/What-tools-do-small-startups-3-40-use-for-Task-Management-Communication-Bug-Tracking/answer/Bob-Troia" target="_blank">check out some of what we use here</a>)</li>
<li>
An obsessive attention to detail and good design sense is a huge plus!</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Compensation and Benefits</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Competitive salary, commensurate with experience</li>
<li>
Great benefits including full medical and dental coverage and 401(k)</li>
<li>
Employee Stock Ownership Program (ESOP)</li>
<li>
Flexible Spending Account (FSA)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>How to Apply</strong></p>
<p>
Interested? Please drop us a line at jobs@beaffinitive.com with the subject line &quot;Technical Project Manager&quot; - be sure to include links to relevant projects you have worked on, as well as your salary requirements/availability.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About Us</strong></p>
<p>
Founded in 2002, Affinitive is word of mouth (WOM) and social media marketing and technology solutions pioneer. Our innovative solutions allow brands to engage, inspire and empower consumers, cultivating loyalty through meaningful and deep engagement across any channel. We are an award winning independent agency with locations in New York City and San Francisco that has created groundbreaking work for major brands across industry verticals. For more information, please visit <a href="http://www.beaffinitive.com" target="_blank">http://www.beaffinitive.com</a></p>
